# Feature modules (`src/features`)

Organize by **screen** (Expo route / tab) plus **capabilities** shared across screens. No barrel `index.ts` files — import the concrete module path.

## Layout

**Screen feature** (one primary route group):

```
features/<screen>/
  components/           # screen UI; nested sections as subfolders
    <section>/          # e.g. standup: workday, activity, notes, voice
  lib/                  # screen-specific domain helpers
    <section>/          # paired with components/<section> when applicable
  hooks/
  context/<name>/       # optional screen orchestration (see react-context-provider.mdc)
  types/                # types for this screen (section types may live here)
```

**Capability feature** (cross-screen data / integration):

```
features/<capability>/
  components/
  lib/
  hooks/
  types/
```

**Example — Generate standup (`standup`)** mirrors a portfolio-style screen:

```
features/standup/
  components/workday/     # date picker, workday section
  components/activity/    # commit terminal, work-type sheet
  components/notes/
  components/voice/
  components/weekly/    # Weekly Summary tab UI
  lib/workday/
  lib/activity/
  lib/notes/
  lib/voice/
  lib/weekly/           # week bounds, aggregation, fetch
  components/standup-draft-panel.tsx   # screen-level sections stay at components/ root
  context/standup/
  lib/compose-standup-markdown.ts      # Standup Update composition
```

## Top-level modules

| Module         | Kind       | Responsibility                                                            |
| -------------- | ---------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `home`         | Screen     | Home tab UI (e.g. standup widget)                                         |
| `standup`      | Screen     | Generate standup + Weekly Summary tab (`components/weekly`, `lib/weekly`) |
| `settings`     | Screen     | Settings, privacy, reminders, account deletion                            |
| `onboarding`   | Screen     | First-time repo setup (route in app)                                      |
| `auth`         | Capability | GitHub OAuth UI and token helpers (session via `@/context`)               |
| `profile`      | Capability | Supabase profile row                                                      |
| `repositories` | Capability | Repo list, picker, GitHub fetch, selection types                          |
| `entitlements` | Capability | Tier limits, upgrade sheet                                                |
| `shell`        | Capability | Tab layout, headers, footers                                              |

Routes stay thin in `src/app/` and import from `@/features/<module>/...` paths.

## Global app shell (not under `features/`)

| Location             | Module                             | Exports / role                                     |
| -------------------- | ---------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| `src/context/theme/` | `index.ts` barrel                  | `AppThemeProvider`, `useAppColorScheme`            |
| `src/context/auth/`  | `index.ts` barrel                  | `AuthProvider`, `useAuth`                          |
| `src/components/`    | `theme-toggle.tsx`                 | `ThemeToggle`                                      |
| `src/hooks/`         | `use-theme-color.ts` (+ `.web.ts`) | Resolved CSS variable colors for native/web        |
| `src/lib/`           | `theme-preference.ts`              | Persisted light/dark preference (used by provider) |
| `src/lib/`           | `theme-colors.ts`                  | Token map for web `useThemeColor`                  |
| `src/lib/`           | `theme.ts`                         | React Navigation `NAV_THEME` (separate from above) |

Wire providers in `src/app/_layout.tsx` from `@/context/auth` and `@/context/theme` (no `src/context/index.ts`).

## Import rules

- **No `index.ts` barrels** under `src/features/` except `features/<screen>/context/<name>/index.ts` (see react-context-provider.mdc). Import concrete paths elsewhere.
- **Cross-feature**: `@/features/<other-feature>/lib/...`, `components/...`, `hooks/...`, or `@/context/...` for app-wide providers.
- **Same feature**: prefer **relative** imports (`../lib/workday/workday`) to avoid Metro self-alias issues; `@/features/standup/...` is fine from routes and other features.
- **Do not** import from removed top-level folders (`workday`, `activity`, `notes`, `voice`, `reminders`, `account` as standalone features).

## Other conventions

- **Shared design system**: `src/components/ui/`, `src/components/icons/`, `src/components/theme-toggle.tsx`.
- **Cross-cutting hooks**: `src/hooks/` — e.g. `use-github-access-token.ts`, `use-theme-color.ts`.
- **Infrastructure**: `src/lib/errors.ts`, `src/lib/utils.ts`, `src/utils/supabase.ts`.
- **Feature-scoped providers** → `features/<screen>/context/<name>/` — see `.cursor/rules/react-context-provider.mdc`.
